WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:07.000
A Big DickUs Production. 
Edited for weird framerate 

2
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:13.000
Spaces added.  
Better for old TVs  

3
00:00:34.827 --> 00:00:36.246
I think we can all agree 

4
00:00:36.329 --> 00:00:38.206
that things were better 
under the Empire. 

5
00:00:39.082 --> 00:00:42.293
Fortunately. I am still here 
to protect you. 

6
00:00:43.294 --> 00:00:45.964
Your communities can thrive 
under my protection. 

7
00:00:47.173 --> 00:00:49.133
You are the lucky few. 

8
00:00:50.176 --> 00:00:52.512
But that which I provide 
is expensive. 

9
00:00:53.555 --> 00:00:55.807
And now 
I must maintain all of it 

10
00:00:55.890 --> 00:00:57.517
without the Empire's support 

11
00:00:57.600 --> 00:00:59.853
until the galaxy realizes 
what they've lost 

12
00:01:00.573 --> 00:01:02.075
and demand our return. 

13
00:01:03.409 --> 00:01:05.662
Long live the Empire. 

14
00:01:08.289 --> 00:01:10.542
Long live the Empire. 

15
00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:13.461
Good. 

16
00:01:14.504 --> 00:01:15.797
Now for the bad news. 

17
00:01:17.841 --> 00:01:19.717
I am raising your tribute. 

18
00:01:22.554 --> 00:01:23.847
But... 

19
00:01:23.930 --> 00:01:27.600
But. Your Excellency. 
we are operating at a loss. 

20
00:01:29.394 --> 00:01:32.480
The trade routes are plagued 
with pirates and thieves. 

21
00:01:32.564 --> 00:01:33.690
ready to attack at-- 

22
00:01:37.861 --> 00:01:40.113
Are you saying 
that my protection is lacking? 

23
00:01:40.905 --> 00:01:42.991
No. Your Excellency. 

24
00:01:44.742 --> 00:01:46.953
I-I am saying that. uh-- 

25
00:01:51.457 --> 00:01:54.335
Perhaps you should all go 
back to your townships 

26
00:01:55.128 --> 00:01:56.838
and focus on solutions. 

27
00:01:57.964 --> 00:01:59.382
not excuses. 

28
00:02:01.354 --> 00:02:02.689
Does that sound reasonable? 

29
00:02:08.278 --> 00:02:10.155
Sounds like a perimeter alarm. 

30
00:02:10.238 --> 00:02:12.073
I'll confirm. 

31
00:02:14.576 --> 00:02:16.828
-I've lost contact. 
~Go check it. 

32
00:02:19.873 --> 00:02:21.416
There's 
nothing to worry about. 

33
00:02:21.499 --> 00:02:23.751
I'll send for reinforcements. 

34
00:02:28.089 --> 00:02:29.966
I will require 
a revenue projection... 

35
00:02:52.739 --> 00:02:54.783
We need backup. On the double! 

36
00:02:54.866 --> 00:02:55.867
Code Red. 

37
00:03:03.136 --> 00:03:04.220
Lay down cover fire. 

38
00:03:06.514 --> 00:03:07.766
Take up arms! 

39
00:03:21.738 --> 00:03:23.531
Long live the Empire! 

40
00:05:06.950 --> 00:05:09.160
What are you waiting for? 
Hop on. 

41
00:05:25.677 --> 00:05:26.845
Hang on. 

42
00:05:53.496 --> 00:05:54.497
Did we get him? 

43
00:05:54.581 --> 00:05:55.999
Not yet. sir. 
But we will. 

44
00:06:04.227 --> 00:06:06.896
-We missed him! He's under us. 
~We have him. 

45
00:06:06.980 --> 00:06:07.981
Fire. 

46
00:06:53.068 --> 00:06:55.153
What's going on? 
Give me a status report. 

47
00:06:55.236 --> 00:06:56.780
Has the target 
been eliminated? 

48
00:06:56.863 --> 00:06:59.074
-We've lost contact. 
~Walker Three is gone. 

49
00:06:59.669 --> 00:07:01.880
-Send everybody! 
~Understood. 

50
00:07:01.963 --> 00:07:03.173
Prepare to engage! 

51
00:07:12.057 --> 00:07:13.141
Get ready. Weapons up. 

52
00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:14.726
Full barrel. Now. let's go. 

53
00:07:49.803 --> 00:07:51.471
Give me a status update. 

54
00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:53.807
Did you see him? 
Have you located him? 

55
00:07:55.266 --> 00:07:56.476
Did you get The Mandalorian? 

56
00:07:58.728 --> 00:07:59.729
Something's up there. 

57
00:08:01.868 --> 00:08:03.203
He's on the roof! 

58
00:08:03.870 --> 00:08:04.871
Can you see him? 

59
00:08:05.538 --> 00:08:06.539
Take him out! 

60
00:08:06.623 --> 00:08:07.624
Get up there. 

61
00:08:08.416 --> 00:08:09.542
But we're pilots. 

62
00:08:09.626 --> 00:08:12.337
-Go now! Do it! 
~Yes. sir. On our way. 

63
00:08:12.420 --> 00:08:13.755
Get up there. 

64
00:08:14.923 --> 00:08:15.924
Set the charges. 

65
00:08:16.007 --> 00:08:17.425
~Prepare for exfil. 
~sir. 

66
00:08:17.509 --> 00:08:20.887
He's breaching the hatch. 
He's breaching the hatch! 

67
00:08:38.655 --> 00:08:39.656
Autopilot. 

68
00:09:12.576 --> 00:09:14.494
I know. I know. 
I need to get the shot. 

69
00:09:44.608 --> 00:09:47.277
You know. it's better 
if you bring 'em in alive. 

70
00:09:54.367 --> 00:09:55.368
You okay? 

71
00:09:57.996 --> 00:10:00.206
You see. you catch the bad guy 

72
00:10:00.260 --> 00:10:02.637
and they tell us 
where the other bad guys are. 

73
00:10:03.346 --> 00:10:05.098
Things went a little sideways. 

74
00:10:10.054 --> 00:10:14.000
The Mandalorian 

75
00:10:15.554 --> 00:10:21.000
and Grogu 

76
00:12:26.054 --> 00:12:28.849
Good luck. 
You're gonna need it. 

77
00:12:37.357 --> 00:12:40.026
Messy. Very messy. 

78
00:12:41.319 --> 00:12:43.947
It was the best I could do 
under the circumstances. 

79
00:12:44.948 --> 00:12:46.950
The problem is. 
we need information. 

80
00:12:47.826 --> 00:12:49.661
Without it. we're never gonna 
get to the bottom of 

81
00:12:49.744 --> 00:12:51.580
what the Empire's up to. 

82
00:12:51.663 --> 00:12:52.664
Just give me time. 

83
00:12:52.747 --> 00:12:55.250
I'll take out every bad guy 
in your deck of cards. 

84
00:12:55.333 --> 00:12:56.877
This isn't about revenge. 

85
00:12:57.377 --> 00:13:00.005
It's about 
preventing another war... 

86
00:13:03.228 --> 00:13:05.897
...and protecting everything 
the Rebellion fought for. 

87
00:13:05.981 --> 00:13:08.191
Does that mean I'm not 
getting paid for this one? 

88
00:13:09.985 --> 00:13:11.820
You're getting paid all right. 

89
00:13:11.903 --> 00:13:12.904
Come with me. 

90
00:13:22.247 --> 00:13:23.457
Impressive. 

91
00:13:23.540 --> 00:13:24.875
Where did you get 
one of these? 

92
00:13:25.584 --> 00:13:27.711
It was from 
a captured Imperial commandant 

93
00:13:27.794 --> 00:13:30.046
who had a big collection 
of vintage vehicles. 

94
00:13:30.547 --> 00:13:33.175
This one is stock. 
Perfectly restored. 

95
00:13:33.842 --> 00:13:35.552
I took it out for a test spin. 

96
00:13:36.136 --> 00:13:38.054
They did a nice job 
on the rebuild. 

97
00:13:40.765 --> 00:13:42.476
This is worth a lot more than 

98
00:13:42.559 --> 00:13:44.060
the bounty on that Imp. 

99
00:13:44.144 --> 00:13:46.771
Well. let's call it an advance 
on the next mission. 

100
00:13:49.024 --> 00:13:50.150
What next mission? 

101
00:13:50.817 --> 00:13:52.277
Commander Coin. 

102
00:13:53.278 --> 00:13:54.780
Our missing Ace of Staves. 

103
00:13:57.199 --> 00:13:58.867
No one knows 
what he looks like 

104
00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:00.964
and most 
believe him to be dead. 

105
00:14:01.673 --> 00:14:04.426
Not a lot to go on. 
What's the play? 

106
00:14:04.509 --> 00:14:07.679
I want you to go to Nal Hutta 
and meet with the Hutts. 

107
00:14:08.263 --> 00:14:10.223
They've agreed to 
lead us to him. 

108
00:14:10.307 --> 00:14:11.308
What's in it for them? 

109
00:14:11.933 --> 00:14:14.269
Their nephew's being held 
against his will 

110
00:14:14.352 --> 00:14:16.855
by another crime syndicate 
on the Outer Rim. 

111
00:14:16.938 --> 00:14:18.148
and they need a professional 

112
00:14:18.231 --> 00:14:19.816
to get him out 
quickly and quietly. 

113
00:14:19.900 --> 00:14:20.901
Where is he? 

114
00:14:21.401 --> 00:14:22.861
They'll only tell you 
in person. 

115
00:14:23.695 --> 00:14:24.696
You got a name? 

116
00:14:25.405 --> 00:14:27.032
His name is Rotta the Hutt. 

117
00:14:27.115 --> 00:14:30.535
The only surviving heir 
of crime lord Jabba the Hutt. 

118
00:14:31.119 --> 00:14:32.370
You ever cross his path? 

119
00:14:32.454 --> 00:14:34.081
I tried not to. 

120
00:14:35.290 --> 00:14:36.291
So... 

121
00:14:37.167 --> 00:14:38.293
do we have a deal? 

122
00:14:38.376 --> 00:14:40.754
I only hunt down 
Imperial war criminals. 

123
00:14:40.837 --> 00:14:44.299
I don't work for gangsters 
anymore. especially the Hutts. 

124
00:14:44.382 --> 00:14:46.885
That's right. you don't. 
You work for us. 

125
00:14:46.968 --> 00:14:49.805
And right now. this is 
what we need you to do. 

126
00:14:50.472 --> 00:14:53.433
You don't want the job. 
I got nothing for you. 

127
00:15:05.207 --> 00:15:06.249
Come aboard. 

128
00:15:08.460 --> 00:15:10.295
May as well 
have a look around. 

129
00:15:15.258 --> 00:15:16.802
Let's go hear the Hutts out. 

130
00:15:17.427 --> 00:15:19.429
I'll even let you fly 
this time. 

131
00:15:19.971 --> 00:15:21.890
I didn't say yes. 

132
00:15:21.973 --> 00:15:23.642
You didn't say no either. 

133
00:15:45.997 --> 00:15:48.166
She's stock. but she's clean. 

134
00:16:05.028 --> 00:16:06.780
Hey. 

135
00:16:06.863 --> 00:16:08.073
Don't touch anything. 

136
00:16:08.615 --> 00:16:09.950
Never touch the buttons. 

137
00:17:53.720 --> 00:17:55.764
Identify yourself. 

138
00:17:57.027 --> 00:17:59.488
Razor Crest. 
requesting clearance. 

139
00:17:59.571 --> 00:18:01.573
I'm here 
by invitation of the Twins. 

140
00:18:02.544 --> 00:18:05.881
Easy on the sticks. 
They're expecting us. 

141
00:18:06.590 --> 00:18:07.841
We should be fine. 

142
00:18:10.260 --> 00:18:11.970
Clearance granted. 

143
00:18:12.054 --> 00:18:13.430
You are clear to approach. 

144
00:18:14.264 --> 00:18:16.308
They've got 
a lot of firepower here. 

145
00:18:16.391 --> 00:18:19.519
Yeah. Looks like 
they hired the Droid Gotra. 

146
00:18:19.603 --> 00:18:21.605
The Hutts 
take security seriously. 

147
00:19:12.709 --> 00:19:14.544
The Hutts have been the 
head of criminal enterprises 

148
00:19:14.628 --> 00:19:16.171
for thousands of years. 

149
00:19:20.676 --> 00:19:22.636
They use 
violence and treachery 

150
00:19:22.719 --> 00:19:23.929
to maintain control. 

151
00:19:25.681 --> 00:19:27.057
Be careful. 

152
00:19:27.140 --> 00:19:31.728
We may be their guests. 
but we are not safe. 

153
00:20:15.742 --> 00:20:18.996
We finally meet the legendary Mandalorian. 

154
00:20:20.205 --> 00:20:24.626
We are so glad you agreed to work for us. 

155
00:20:25.210 --> 00:20:27.462
You will be very rich. 

156
00:20:27.546 --> 00:20:29.089
I don't work for you. 

157
00:20:29.172 --> 00:20:30.674
I work for the New Republic. 

158
00:20:31.550 --> 00:20:32.634
I'm told you can lead us 

159
00:20:32.718 --> 00:20:35.012
to the Imperial fugitive 
Commander Coin. 

160
00:20:35.887 --> 00:20:38.140
Of course. Mando. 

161
00:20:38.223 --> 00:20:39.975
I understand 
your nephew. Rotta. 

162
00:20:40.058 --> 00:20:41.351
has been kidnapped. 

163
00:20:41.685 --> 00:20:44.730
Yes. our poor nephew has been taken. 

164
00:20:45.647 --> 00:20:48.275
He fell in with a bad crowd. 

165
00:20:48.692 --> 00:20:51.361
We are heartbroken. 

166
00:20:52.112 --> 00:20:54.865
Think of how you would feel 

167
00:20:54.948 --> 00:20:58.035
if your little one went missing. 

168
00:21:00.299 --> 00:21:01.800
What does he look like? 

169
00:21:01.884 --> 00:21:03.093
Do you have an image? 

170
00:21:03.385 --> 00:21:04.720
Ah. yes. 

171
00:21:05.220 --> 00:21:09.016
The only image we have is from long ago. 

172
00:21:15.606 --> 00:21:19.318
He's had a growth spurt since then. 

173
00:21:20.068 --> 00:21:23.655
Okay. 
I'll rescue your nephew. 

174
00:21:23.739 --> 00:21:24.740
Where is he being held? 

175
00:21:25.407 --> 00:21:30.329
You will find him on the moon of Shakari. 

176
00:21:30.913 --> 00:21:32.331
It shall be done. 

177
00:21:51.850 --> 00:21:53.602
We're about to 
come out of hyperspace 

178
00:21:53.685 --> 00:21:55.020
in the Shakari system. 

179
00:21:55.646 --> 00:21:57.814
To state 
the obvious. you are operating 

180
00:21:57.898 --> 00:22:00.067
outside the jurisdiction 
of the New Republic. 

181
00:22:01.163 --> 00:22:05.042
If things get messy. I can't 
call in an X-wing strike. 

182
00:22:05.584 --> 00:22:07.461
I know the drill. 

183
00:22:08.337 --> 00:22:11.965
Before going into harm's way. 
check your armor first. 

184
00:22:12.049 --> 00:22:14.510
It's gotta fit snug 
so it doesn't slide. 

185
00:22:14.593 --> 00:22:17.221
but not so tight that it 
restricts your movement. 

186
00:22:17.930 --> 00:22:19.097
Got it? 

187
00:22:20.599 --> 00:22:22.100
How's that feel? 

188
00:22:45.832 --> 00:22:47.626
All right. Zeb. drop us here. 

189
00:23:44.236 --> 00:23:45.237
Yes? 

190
00:23:45.320 --> 00:23:47.072
I'll take a flat-meat fry 
for the little one. 

191
00:23:47.156 --> 00:23:48.866
Got it. Okay. got it. got it. 

192
00:23:48.949 --> 00:23:50.409
Flat-meat fry. huh? 

193
00:23:52.953 --> 00:23:54.538
Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah. 

194
00:24:00.764 --> 00:24:02.057
Whoa. 

195
00:24:02.141 --> 00:24:03.809
That's quite an 
impressive denomination. 

196
00:24:03.892 --> 00:24:05.269
I'm not sure I've got 
change for that. 

197
00:24:05.352 --> 00:24:06.687
You can keep the change. 

198
00:24:06.770 --> 00:24:08.397
I'm new to these parts. 

199
00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:10.607
I can use some information. 

200
00:24:10.691 --> 00:24:13.068
Yeah. for this price. I'll 
tell you whatever you want. 

201
00:24:13.569 --> 00:24:14.987
I'm looking for a Hutt. 

202
00:24:15.070 --> 00:24:17.573
Shh. Don't mention that name. 
Don't say that. 

203
00:24:17.656 --> 00:24:19.074
What. are you trying 
to get us both killed? 

204
00:24:19.158 --> 00:24:21.243
Here. Keep your credits. 
Food's on me. 

205
00:24:21.785 --> 00:24:23.579
Go away. Thank you. 

206
00:24:23.662 --> 00:24:26.248
Okay. never happened. 
Let's go. Nothing to see here. 

207
00:24:26.331 --> 00:24:27.916
Damn Mandalorian. 
talking like that. 

208
00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:30.252
Just out in the open. 
he talks like... What is this? 

209
00:24:30.335 --> 00:24:33.005
No. no. no. No. no. no. no. 
I don't want your credits. 

210
00:24:33.088 --> 00:24:34.506
'cause I didn't give you 
any information. 

211
00:24:34.590 --> 00:24:36.008
His name is Rotta. 

212
00:24:36.884 --> 00:24:37.885
Really? 

213
00:24:40.179 --> 00:24:41.430
Something funny? 

214
00:24:41.513 --> 00:24:42.973
Yeah. yeah. 
Everybody... 

215
00:24:43.056 --> 00:24:44.892
Everybody knows 
Rotta the Hutt. 

216
00:24:44.975 --> 00:24:47.102
That guy's a monster. 

217
00:25:33.368 --> 00:25:34.745
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta! 

218
00:25:34.828 --> 00:25:36.997
He doesn't seem like 
a prisoner to me. 

219
00:25:39.082 --> 00:25:40.751
...Rotta! 

220
00:26:21.011 --> 00:26:22.554
Are you here to kill me? 

221
00:26:23.430 --> 00:26:25.140
I'm here to rescue you. 

222
00:26:27.267 --> 00:26:29.645
What makes you think 
I need rescuing? 

223
00:26:29.728 --> 00:26:31.605
Your aunt and uncle 
hired me to find you. 

224
00:26:32.815 --> 00:26:36.819
Yeah. I see. Well. thank you. 
but I don't require rescuing. 

225
00:26:37.444 --> 00:26:39.863
Tomorrow's the last match 
in my contract and after that. 

226
00:26:39.947 --> 00:26:41.657
my debt will be paid. 

227
00:26:41.740 --> 00:26:43.409
I'll be a free agent. 

228
00:26:46.829 --> 00:26:48.163
Paid to who? 

229
00:26:50.999 --> 00:26:52.000
Who's he? 

230
00:26:53.127 --> 00:26:54.962
Don't stare. 

231
00:26:55.045 --> 00:26:57.005
It's okay. What's your name? 

232
00:26:57.089 --> 00:26:59.049
He doesn't talk. 

233
00:26:59.103 --> 00:27:00.729
Who do you have to pay? 

234
00:27:00.813 --> 00:27:02.189
Can I feed him? 

235
00:27:06.193 --> 00:27:07.403
Sure. 

236
00:27:07.486 --> 00:27:08.904
Who do you have to pay? 

237
00:27:14.702 --> 00:27:16.120
Lord Janu. 

238
00:27:17.496 --> 00:27:19.081
I don't know the name. 

239
00:27:19.164 --> 00:27:20.541
You should. 

240
00:27:20.624 --> 00:27:23.377
He runs the Syndicate 
on all the moons of Shakari. 

241
00:27:26.004 --> 00:27:27.423
He signed me to his stable. 

242
00:27:27.506 --> 00:27:29.675
He bankrolled 
my board and training. 

243
00:27:29.758 --> 00:27:31.635
He keeps you in a cage. 

244
00:27:31.719 --> 00:27:32.845
He treats me well. 

245
00:27:33.387 --> 00:27:36.181
And after tomorrow night. 
I'll be my own man. 

246
00:27:36.265 --> 00:27:38.851
And with the following 
he got me as a promoter. 

247
00:27:38.934 --> 00:27:41.019
not only will my debt be paid. 

248
00:27:41.103 --> 00:27:42.604
but I'll be rich 
by the solstice. 

249
00:27:42.688 --> 00:27:44.815
Grogu. heel! 

250
00:27:47.609 --> 00:27:50.112
Don't worry. 
I'm not my father. 

251
00:27:55.576 --> 00:27:57.953
You know how hard it is 
to be your own man 

252
00:27:58.037 --> 00:27:59.913
when your father is 
Jabba the Hutt? 

253
00:28:05.544 --> 00:28:07.963
You see them 
cheering for me out there? 

254
00:28:08.017 --> 00:28:09.018
For me. 

255
00:28:09.768 --> 00:28:12.980
It's the first time 
I'm not living in his shadow. 

256
00:28:13.063 --> 00:28:15.107
That's why 
I fight in the pits. 

257
00:28:15.607 --> 00:28:18.902
They feared him. 
but they cheer for me. 

258
00:28:20.696 --> 00:28:21.947
So. no... 

259
00:28:22.656 --> 00:28:24.533
I don't need to be rescued. 

260
00:28:28.537 --> 00:28:30.289
Where can I find Lord Janu? 

261
00:28:31.999 --> 00:28:33.876
Thank you. 
Closed for the night. 

262
00:28:38.714 --> 00:28:40.883
What the hell's he thinking? 
Damn Mandalorians. 

263
00:28:40.966 --> 00:28:42.551
Mandalorians. they don't even 
come from here. 

264
00:28:42.634 --> 00:28:44.219
He's going around. talking-- 

265
00:28:45.471 --> 00:28:48.474
I just wanna know 
where I can find Lord Janu. 

266
00:28:48.557 --> 00:28:51.810
Don't say that. 
Do not say that name. 

267
00:28:51.894 --> 00:28:53.437
Stop saying it. 

268
00:28:53.520 --> 00:28:55.647
I recommend you calm down. 

269
00:28:56.190 --> 00:28:57.816
Just. please. please. 
don't kill me. Don't kill me. 

270
00:28:57.900 --> 00:28:59.735
I've got... I've got 
12 little ones at home. 

271
00:28:59.788 --> 00:29:01.832
smaller than him. 
It's... They're smaller. 

272
00:29:02.666 --> 00:29:04.626
Yeah. it's just... 

273
00:29:04.710 --> 00:29:07.087
I pay him protection. okay? 

274
00:29:07.171 --> 00:29:08.172
We all do. 

275
00:29:08.255 --> 00:29:09.798
I barely make a living. 
to be honest. 

276
00:29:09.882 --> 00:29:12.301
-But at least I'm alive. 
~Who collects for him? 

277
00:29:12.384 --> 00:29:14.053
I don't know. 
Different people come in. 

278
00:29:14.136 --> 00:29:16.221
Sometimes they come here. 
sometimes I do a drop myself. 

279
00:29:16.305 --> 00:29:17.848
~What do I know? 
~Where? 

280
00:29:17.931 --> 00:29:20.643
~Where what? 
~Where do you do the drops? 

281
00:29:20.726 --> 00:29:22.102
I don't... Some pla... 
Sometimes. 

282
00:29:22.186 --> 00:29:24.104
I go down to... 
...different places. 

283
00:29:24.188 --> 00:29:26.148
Usually... Sometimes 
I go to the salt bar 

284
00:29:26.231 --> 00:29:28.025
under Korvin Station. 

285
00:29:28.108 --> 00:29:30.069
And then there's 
other places too. You go to... 

286
00:29:30.152 --> 00:29:31.820
You know. You know. 
I go around. 

287
00:29:33.405 --> 00:29:35.282
No. I don't want it. 
I don't want it. 

288
00:29:35.366 --> 00:29:36.742
I didn't give you 
any information. 

289
00:29:36.825 --> 00:29:38.577
~I was just talking. 
-That's not for information. 

290
00:29:39.119 --> 00:29:40.329
It's to cover his tab. 

291
00:30:26.178 --> 00:30:27.680
I'm looking for Lord Janu. 

292
00:30:32.309 --> 00:30:34.228
Maybe you made a mistake. 

293
00:30:36.188 --> 00:30:38.857
Maybe you remember wrong 
and think you know me. 

294
00:30:42.403 --> 00:30:44.613
Maybe you just walked through 
the wrong door. 

295
00:30:45.948 --> 00:30:48.325
Well. 
I'm not here to buy salt. 

296
00:30:49.118 --> 00:30:50.327
Salt? 

297
00:30:51.161 --> 00:30:52.538
We don't sell salt. 

298
00:30:53.455 --> 00:30:54.581
It's on the ration. 

299
00:30:57.042 --> 00:30:59.044
How much 
for the shoulder candy? 

300
00:31:01.892 --> 00:31:03.769
Would look real pretty 
in a cage. 

301
00:31:04.853 --> 00:31:06.522
I'm here to see Lord Janu. 

302
00:31:07.815 --> 00:31:09.900
I won't repeat myself again. 

303
00:31:58.711 --> 00:32:01.005
It seems you've 
earned your salt today. 

304
00:32:04.174 --> 00:32:05.217
I'm Janu. 

305
00:32:06.302 --> 00:32:08.262
Come to the back 
and pick out a crystal. 

306
00:32:08.762 --> 00:32:09.763
Hogsbreth. 

307
00:32:11.599 --> 00:32:13.142
have the boys clean up. 

308
00:32:14.435 --> 00:32:16.562
Make sure 
I don't lose any pets. 

309
00:32:35.247 --> 00:32:36.248
Here. 

310
00:32:36.999 --> 00:32:38.167
Choose one. 

311
00:32:38.250 --> 00:32:40.878
Salt is of no value to me 
where I'm from. 

312
00:32:40.961 --> 00:32:42.963
But here 
it's worth a small fortune. 

313
00:32:43.047 --> 00:32:46.300
because it's rationed 
by the politicians. 

314
00:32:47.009 --> 00:32:48.510
Which makes it rare. 

315
00:32:49.970 --> 00:32:51.639
As are you. Mandalorian. 

316
00:32:53.224 --> 00:32:55.309
Have you ever considered 
fighting in the pits? 

317
00:32:55.392 --> 00:32:57.394
I try to avoid violence. 

318
00:32:58.782 --> 00:32:59.992
'Course you do. 

319
00:33:00.993 --> 00:33:02.203
I do as well. 

320
00:33:04.038 --> 00:33:05.706
So what brings you to 
this establishment 

321
00:33:05.789 --> 00:33:07.374
if you're not 
in the market for salt? 

322
00:33:07.458 --> 00:33:10.419
I wanna buy out the contract 
on a fighter from your stable. 

323
00:33:11.045 --> 00:33:13.714
Perhaps you would consider 
joining my stable instead? 

324
00:33:19.887 --> 00:33:22.431
This buys a lot of salt 
where I'm from. 

325
00:33:22.515 --> 00:33:23.682
I am offering you this 

326
00:33:23.766 --> 00:33:26.560
in exchange for the fighting 
contract on Rotta the Hutt. 

327
00:33:26.644 --> 00:33:28.687
My dear boy. 
there's no price high enough 

328
00:33:28.771 --> 00:33:30.898
to buy him out of 
his last fights. 

329
00:33:30.981 --> 00:33:33.192
I've been grooming that 
little prince for many cycles. 

330
00:33:33.275 --> 00:33:34.902
setting him up 
for tomorrow's match. 

331
00:33:34.985 --> 00:33:36.028
Take the credits. 

332
00:33:36.111 --> 00:33:38.322
It's his last fight 
for you anyway. 

333
00:33:39.448 --> 00:33:40.699
It's his last fight ever. 

334
00:33:42.326 --> 00:33:43.786
I've collected 
the most deadly creatures 

335
00:33:43.869 --> 00:33:45.371
from across the galaxy. 

336
00:33:45.913 --> 00:33:47.873
He's fighting a Dejarik match? 

337
00:33:48.415 --> 00:33:49.542
Yes. 

338
00:33:50.251 --> 00:33:51.835
He will die tomorrow. 

339
00:33:53.003 --> 00:33:54.505
And a select few know it. 

340
00:33:55.381 --> 00:33:56.715
Here's my gift to you: 

341
00:33:57.758 --> 00:33:58.759
take those credits. 

342
00:34:00.189 --> 00:34:02.024
bet it all 
on the death of the Hutt. 

343
00:34:02.900 --> 00:34:04.318
In exchange. 

344
00:34:04.401 --> 00:34:07.947
all I ask is that you 
consider fighting in my pit. 

345
00:34:08.030 --> 00:34:10.199
The people of Shakari 
would pay any price 

346
00:34:10.282 --> 00:34:12.159
to see the rarest of sights. 

347
00:34:12.243 --> 00:34:15.037
one of the legendary 
Mandalorian warriors 

348
00:34:15.120 --> 00:34:17.498
engaging in blood sport. 

349
00:34:26.173 --> 00:34:27.591
This should more than cover 

350
00:34:28.175 --> 00:34:30.135
our little misunderstanding 
out there. 

351
00:34:34.098 --> 00:34:36.225
All I ask 
is that you consider my offer. 

352
00:34:37.935 --> 00:34:40.229
Could make us both very rich. 

353
00:35:14.525 --> 00:35:17.361
Looks like we're gonna have to 
do this the hard way. 

354
00:36:46.170 --> 00:36:47.546
What? 

355
00:36:48.589 --> 00:36:50.174
Janu's planning on 
killing you. 

356
00:36:50.257 --> 00:36:51.383
I'm here to get you out. 

357
00:36:54.720 --> 00:36:57.640
Tomorrow's my last fight. 
I'll be free after I win. 

358
00:36:57.723 --> 00:37:01.102
The fix is in. 
It's a Dejarik match. 

359
00:37:01.155 --> 00:37:02.823
He will keep 
throwing opponents at you 

360
00:37:02.907 --> 00:37:03.991
until you die. 

361
00:37:04.075 --> 00:37:05.826
Why should I believe you? 

362
00:37:06.327 --> 00:37:08.662
You were sent by my aunt 
and uncle who want me dead. 

363
00:37:08.746 --> 00:37:10.372
They want you back. 

364
00:37:10.456 --> 00:37:11.916
You're embarrassing them. 

365
00:37:11.999 --> 00:37:13.084
The Twins want me dead 

366
00:37:13.167 --> 00:37:15.753
because I'm heir 
to the throne. not them. 

367
00:37:15.836 --> 00:37:17.379
But I don't want it. 

368
00:37:17.463 --> 00:37:19.840
I don't wanna be anything 
like my father. 

369
00:37:20.883 --> 00:37:23.969
When I first started fighting. 
the people all booed me. 

370
00:37:24.053 --> 00:37:25.513
They wanted to see me die 

371
00:37:25.596 --> 00:37:27.681
because I'm the son 
of Jabba the Hutt. 

372
00:37:27.765 --> 00:37:29.558
Then I won 
and became a champion 

373
00:37:29.642 --> 00:37:31.727
and they slowly 
began to cheer. 

374
00:37:31.811 --> 00:37:33.813
They realized 
I'm not my father. 

375
00:37:33.896 --> 00:37:35.314
I'm my own man. 

376
00:37:35.398 --> 00:37:37.733
and I'm not afraid to fight 
for what I have. 

377
00:37:37.817 --> 00:37:40.653
To earn it. 
To prove myself to everyone. 

378
00:37:41.570 --> 00:37:44.198
Kid. fighting's not a sport. 

379
00:37:44.281 --> 00:37:46.117
It's a last resort. 

380
00:37:46.200 --> 00:37:48.285
Now come with me 
before things get ugly. 

381
00:37:48.369 --> 00:37:50.704
Guards. he's back! 

382
00:37:54.166 --> 00:37:57.169
Get out. Get out! 

383
00:38:42.184 --> 00:38:44.478
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta! 

384
00:39:04.510 --> 00:39:06.429
Rotta! 

385
00:39:33.539 --> 00:39:34.957
I don't want to fight you. 

386
00:39:35.875 --> 00:39:37.918
Then you're in for a long day! 

387
00:39:47.386 --> 00:39:48.429
Yes! 

388
00:40:14.008 --> 00:40:16.761
I'm not going to kill you. 

389
00:40:16.844 --> 00:40:18.554
I'm here to rescue you. 

390
00:41:05.351 --> 00:41:07.645
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! 

391
00:41:07.698 --> 00:41:10.409
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! 

392
00:41:10.493 --> 00:41:13.120
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! 

393
00:41:13.204 --> 00:41:15.998
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! 

394
00:41:16.082 --> 00:41:18.459
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill! 

395
00:41:18.542 --> 00:41:20.294
Kill! Kill! Kill... 

396
00:41:20.378 --> 00:41:21.545
I yield. 

397
00:41:26.133 --> 00:41:28.219
Rotta the Hutt has won. 

398
00:41:28.302 --> 00:41:30.972
Now you owe him his freedom. 

399
00:41:38.020 --> 00:41:40.106
Rotta the Hutt has won. 

400
00:41:40.856 --> 00:41:42.775
Now he is free... 

401
00:41:45.444 --> 00:41:46.570
to die! 

402
00:42:32.336 --> 00:42:35.131
Our only chance 
is to work together. 

403
00:43:59.363 --> 00:44:01.115
Watch out for the little one. 

404
00:44:01.199 --> 00:44:02.491
Yeah. I got this. 

405
00:45:13.616 --> 00:45:14.617
We should go now. 

406
00:45:14.700 --> 00:45:15.868
Now! 

407
00:45:46.190 --> 00:45:47.191
Are you good? 

408
00:45:48.693 --> 00:45:51.112
Don't worry. buddy. 
We're getting out of here. 

409
00:46:14.021 --> 00:46:16.232
You were right. 
The fix was in. 

410
00:46:16.315 --> 00:46:17.775
Let's get you out of here. 

411
00:46:19.527 --> 00:46:21.154
I'm gonna find us a ride. 

412
00:46:43.468 --> 00:46:44.719
Sorry. Mando. 

413
00:46:44.802 --> 00:46:46.262
I can't go back. 

414
00:47:09.660 --> 00:47:11.496
Zeb. I got a runner. 

415
00:48:01.944 --> 00:48:04.155
Okay. you got me. 

416
00:48:05.198 --> 00:48:07.116
Can't blame a guy for trying. 

417
00:48:25.134 --> 00:48:27.345
We're about 
to jump to hyperspace. 

418
00:48:27.428 --> 00:48:28.846
Where are you bringing me? 

419
00:48:28.930 --> 00:48:30.681
It's not safe 
to keep you chained up. 

420
00:48:31.182 --> 00:48:32.391
If I unlock you. 

421
00:48:32.475 --> 00:48:34.435
can we agree 
to no funny stuff? 

422
00:48:34.519 --> 00:48:36.562
Are you bringing me 
to Nal Hutta? 

423
00:48:36.646 --> 00:48:37.730
This is an old ship. 

424
00:48:37.814 --> 00:48:39.732
Sometimes things 
get a little bouncy. 

425
00:48:40.316 --> 00:48:42.610
My aunt and uncle 
were scared of my father. 

426
00:48:42.693 --> 00:48:44.695
They've always 
been cruel to me. 

427
00:48:44.779 --> 00:48:46.906
Now that they control 
his criminal empire. 

428
00:48:46.989 --> 00:48:48.658
they need me eliminated. 

429
00:48:48.741 --> 00:48:50.827
You bring me to them. 
I'm a dead man. 

430
00:48:50.910 --> 00:48:51.953
You don't know that. 

431
00:48:52.036 --> 00:48:53.121
If you let me go. 

432
00:48:53.204 --> 00:48:54.956
you'll never 
hear from me again. 

433
00:48:55.456 --> 00:48:57.125
It's a big galaxy. 

434
00:48:57.208 --> 00:48:58.418
I can disappear. 

435
00:48:58.471 --> 00:49:00.139
Sorry. kid. 

436
00:49:00.223 --> 00:49:01.808
I was hired to do a job. 

437
00:49:02.392 --> 00:49:04.602
I don't know how 
you sleep at night. 

438
00:49:04.685 --> 00:49:06.270
working for those monsters. 

439
00:49:06.813 --> 00:49:08.648
I don't work for them. 

440
00:49:08.731 --> 00:49:10.775
I work for the New Republic. 

441
00:49:10.858 --> 00:49:13.277
They hired me. not the Twins. 

442
00:49:13.778 --> 00:49:15.405
When I bring you back. 
they're giving me 

443
00:49:15.488 --> 00:49:17.198
the whereabouts 
of Commander Coin. 

444
00:49:17.281 --> 00:49:20.243
a high-ranking ex-Imperial 
operating on the Outer Rim. 

445
00:49:20.743 --> 00:49:22.036
It's Janu. 

446
00:49:23.162 --> 00:49:26.040
The man you're looking for 
is Janu. 

447
00:49:26.124 --> 00:49:27.500
Lord Janu Coin. 

448
00:49:28.000 --> 00:49:29.460
That's who the Hutts 
are gonna give you. 

449
00:49:29.544 --> 00:49:30.837
He's ex-Imperial. 

450
00:49:30.920 --> 00:49:33.256
That can't be. 
The Twins would've told me. 

451
00:49:33.339 --> 00:49:34.966
I saw stormtroopers. 

452
00:49:35.883 --> 00:49:37.510
He brought me 
to his estate once 

453
00:49:37.593 --> 00:49:38.678
to celebrate a big win 

454
00:49:38.761 --> 00:49:41.013
and there were 
stormtroopers everywhere. 

455
00:49:41.097 --> 00:49:43.057
If you don't believe me 
and you don't get him now. 

456
00:49:43.141 --> 00:49:44.559
you won't get another shot. 

457
00:49:45.059 --> 00:49:46.728
In fact. 
it might already be too late. 

458
00:49:47.603 --> 00:49:49.147
That's quite a story. 

459
00:49:49.230 --> 00:49:50.940
Why should I believe you? 

460
00:49:51.023 --> 00:49:54.068
You're a bounty hunter. 
you know when someone's lying. 

461
00:49:56.446 --> 00:49:58.031
Am I lying... 

462
00:49:58.084 --> 00:49:59.752
or am I telling the truth? 

463
00:50:20.481 --> 00:50:21.607
That's it. 

464
00:50:22.191 --> 00:50:24.110
That's Janu Coin's compound. 

465
00:50:24.944 --> 00:50:27.530
Could be big boy's 
telling the truth. 

466
00:50:27.613 --> 00:50:30.283
The place is lousy 
with stormtroopers. 

467
00:50:33.745 --> 00:50:34.954
How many did you see 

468
00:50:35.038 --> 00:50:36.039
when you were in there? 

469
00:50:36.998 --> 00:50:37.999
A lot. 

470
00:50:39.083 --> 00:50:40.418
You're gonna need 
a lot of backup 

471
00:50:40.501 --> 00:50:42.337
if you're actually 
thinking of going in. 

472
00:50:43.254 --> 00:50:44.380
Uh-huh. 

473
00:50:45.673 --> 00:50:47.633
Get word 
to all our foot soldiers 

474
00:50:47.717 --> 00:50:49.635
on the dark side of Shakari. 

475
00:50:49.719 --> 00:50:53.389
I want eyes on the starport 
and all the freight lanes. 

476
00:50:53.473 --> 00:50:54.474
Lean on the mayor. 

477
00:50:54.557 --> 00:50:56.809
Nothing takes off 
or lands until we find them. 

478
00:50:56.893 --> 00:50:58.978
Muster 
my personal security forces. 

479
00:50:59.604 --> 00:51:01.814
We're going to hit the streets 
in full armor. 

480
00:51:01.868 --> 00:51:03.119
I don't want to 
take any chances 

481
00:51:03.202 --> 00:51:04.579
when it comes to 
The Mandalorian. 

482
00:51:04.662 --> 00:51:06.956
I've heard many things 
about those monsters. 

483
00:51:07.457 --> 00:51:08.791
It's all true. 

484
00:51:10.293 --> 00:51:12.462
Imperial Commander Janu Coin. 

485
00:51:12.545 --> 00:51:14.297
I'm here on behalf 
of the New Republic 

486
00:51:14.380 --> 00:51:15.923
to bring you to justice. 

487
00:51:16.549 --> 00:51:19.052
I'm afraid we're outside 
of your jurisdiction. 

488
00:51:19.802 --> 00:51:21.095
Take him! 

489
00:51:25.933 --> 00:51:27.518
~Set blasters On full. 
-Hurry! 

490
00:52:26.869 --> 00:52:28.705
I can bring you in warm... 

491
00:52:30.259 --> 00:52:32.178
or I can bring you in cold. 

492
00:52:56.202 --> 00:52:57.578
Grogu. 

493
00:52:59.092 --> 00:53:00.218
Rotta. 

494
00:53:00.927 --> 00:53:02.387
Rotta. come in. 

495
00:53:02.470 --> 00:53:03.846
Does anyone read me? 

496
00:53:05.431 --> 00:53:06.641
I'm up. I'm up. 

497
00:53:06.724 --> 00:53:08.893
I need you 
to fire up the drives. 

498
00:53:08.977 --> 00:53:10.061
Fire up the drives. 

499
00:53:10.144 --> 00:53:11.896
~We have company. 
~Received. 

500
00:53:12.647 --> 00:53:14.983
I don't know how to fly. 
Do you know how to fly? 

501
00:53:15.775 --> 00:53:17.443
Neither of us know how to fly. 

502
00:53:17.527 --> 00:53:19.237
and I can't even 
fit in the cockpit. 

503
00:53:25.743 --> 00:53:29.122
Grogu. I need you to go 
to the control panel. 

504
00:53:29.205 --> 00:53:31.207
Remember the buttons 
I told you never to touch? 

505
00:53:31.291 --> 00:53:32.917
I'm gonna need you 
to touch them. 

506
00:53:33.001 --> 00:53:35.753
Look for 
the ignition relay cutoff. 

507
00:53:35.837 --> 00:53:37.964
It's next to 
the fuel differential readout. 

508
00:53:38.506 --> 00:53:41.301
which is between 
the pump compression gauge 

509
00:53:41.384 --> 00:53:43.177
and the primary 
reserve indic-- 

510
00:53:45.763 --> 00:53:47.181
Whoa. 

511
00:53:47.265 --> 00:53:49.767
No. Don't touch 
the missile battery switch. 

512
00:53:49.851 --> 00:53:51.477
That's why there's 
a safety guard on it. 

513
00:53:51.561 --> 00:53:53.688
Do you see 
the fuel readout display? 

514
00:53:53.771 --> 00:53:55.231
Remember 
I showed you that one? 

515
00:53:55.315 --> 00:53:56.482
It's on the other side 

516
00:53:56.566 --> 00:53:58.901
of the manual control 
surface calibration un-- 

517
00:54:01.583 --> 00:54:03.459
I don't think 
he knows what he's doing. 

518
00:54:25.857 --> 00:54:26.983
Get out. 

519
00:54:31.529 --> 00:54:34.032
Get going. 
They're shooting at you too. 

520
00:54:42.415 --> 00:54:44.375
Good job. buddy. Strap in. 

521
00:55:09.037 --> 00:55:10.580
I like this kid. 

522
00:55:21.257 --> 00:55:23.092
Come on. Come on. 

523
00:55:35.355 --> 00:55:37.232
Get us out of atmosphere 
and jump! 

524
00:55:37.315 --> 00:55:38.358
Get up here. 

525
00:55:38.441 --> 00:55:40.443
I need you to bypass 
the exhaust restrictors. 

526
00:55:54.290 --> 00:55:56.709
This old junker's 
gonna get us killed. 

527
00:55:56.793 --> 00:55:57.919
I need more power. 

528
00:55:57.972 --> 00:56:00.642
Disable the safety panel 
so I can override the limiter. 

529
00:56:00.725 --> 00:56:03.394
How? I'm a pilot. 
not a meknek. 

530
00:56:03.478 --> 00:56:05.605
Just rip out 
the whole brain board. 

531
00:56:11.110 --> 00:56:12.695
Everything okay up there? 

532
00:56:12.779 --> 00:56:14.197
Perfect. 

533
00:56:20.912 --> 00:56:23.665
I told you to strap in. 
Always wear your seat belt. 

534
00:56:33.091 --> 00:56:34.968
Take it easy up there! 

535
00:56:41.349 --> 00:56:42.684
There we go. 

536
00:58:14.609 --> 00:58:16.444
That doesn't look like a Hutt. 

537
00:58:16.468 --> 00:58:19.179
This is Imperial Commander 
Janu Coin. 

538
00:58:19.262 --> 00:58:22.432
He's full of information and 
ready to sing like a Yuzzum. 

539
00:58:22.515 --> 00:58:24.184
Isn't that right. Coin? 

540
00:58:24.267 --> 00:58:25.685
I demand 
an attorney be present 

541
00:58:25.769 --> 00:58:26.936
if I'm to be questioned. 

542
00:58:27.604 --> 00:58:28.605
You see? 

543
00:58:29.105 --> 00:58:30.815
He's full of secrets. 

544
00:58:31.649 --> 00:58:33.443
You were supposed 
to bring back Rotta. 

545
00:58:34.569 --> 00:58:36.821
We had an arrangement 
with the Twins. 

546
00:58:36.905 --> 00:58:38.990
This is your Ace of Staves. 

547
00:58:39.741 --> 00:58:41.743
This is who they were 
going to lead you to. 

548
00:58:42.452 --> 00:58:43.578
And then tip him off. 

549
00:58:43.661 --> 00:58:46.289
sell you out and collect 
credits from both sides. 

550
00:58:47.499 --> 00:58:48.875
Take him away. 

551
00:58:53.963 --> 00:58:55.882
Intelligence 
has been cultivating 

552
00:58:55.965 --> 00:58:59.135
a relationship with the Hutts 
for a very long time. 

553
00:58:59.189 --> 00:59:00.690
and you crossed them. 

554
00:59:02.150 --> 00:59:03.943
The Twins can hold a grudge. 

555
00:59:04.027 --> 00:59:05.278
I made a call. 

556
00:59:05.361 --> 00:59:06.988
I got you the big prize. 

557
00:59:07.530 --> 00:59:09.491
The Twins can rot in hell. 

558
00:59:09.574 --> 00:59:10.950
Well. you missed out 
on them paying you 

559
00:59:11.034 --> 00:59:12.994
a big bounty for their nephew. 

560
00:59:13.078 --> 00:59:14.204
Hmm... 

561
00:59:14.287 --> 00:59:15.580
So be it. 

562
00:59:17.582 --> 00:59:19.626
Well. I'll see if 
I can hit up Command 
563
-01:59:57.230 --> 00:59:21.628 
for a fee 
for the capture of Coin. 

563
00:59:21.711 --> 00:59:24.214
Don't worry about it. 
It's on me. 

564
00:59:25.006 --> 00:59:26.591
This one got messy. 

565
00:59:26.674 --> 00:59:27.926
I'm taking a break. 

566
00:59:29.511 --> 00:59:30.845
I understand. 

567
00:59:31.888 --> 00:59:33.098
Mando. 

568
00:59:35.767 --> 00:59:37.018
Good job. 

569
01:00:59.768 --> 01:01:01.770
We're gonna 
pull the restrictor plates. 

570
01:01:01.853 --> 01:01:04.522
The first one should be 
just past the return line. 

571
01:01:04.606 --> 01:01:06.107
That's it. 

572
01:01:06.191 --> 01:01:08.318
There should be three more. 

573
01:01:20.914 --> 01:01:23.208
Okay. okay. Okey-doke. 

574
01:01:29.339 --> 01:01:30.340
Okay. okay. 

575
01:01:30.423 --> 01:01:31.758
Thanks for coming. 

576
01:01:32.425 --> 01:01:33.718
No problem. 

577
01:01:33.802 --> 01:01:36.596
I'm looking to make some 
performance modifications. 

578
01:01:36.679 --> 01:01:38.473
I need to cut out 
dead weight for speed. 

579
01:01:39.891 --> 01:01:42.227
Pull out anything 
that doesn't make her go. 

580
01:01:43.061 --> 01:01:44.062
Hey! 

581
01:01:44.145 --> 01:01:45.480
Hey. Hey. 

582
01:01:45.563 --> 01:01:46.564
No. don't touch me! 

583
01:01:46.648 --> 01:01:48.983
Heel. 

584
01:01:49.067 --> 01:01:50.777
~the horrible baby. 
~the bad baby. 

585
01:01:50.860 --> 01:01:52.821
Stay. 

586
01:01:52.904 --> 01:01:54.239
I purged the fuel lines. 

587
01:01:54.322 --> 01:01:55.990
I wanna remove 
all the restrictors 

588
01:01:56.044 --> 01:01:57.629
and unplug the exhaust. 

589
01:01:57.712 --> 01:02:00.799
~Got it. Yeah. yeah. 
~No problem. yeah. I Got it. 

590
01:02:01.424 --> 01:02:02.676
~No problem. 
~yeah. Okey-doke. 

591
01:02:04.135 --> 01:02:05.387
You wanna go help them? 

592
01:02:07.263 --> 01:02:09.015
Do you promise to play nice? 

593
01:02:10.392 --> 01:02:12.477
All right. Go. 

594
01:02:19.109 --> 01:02:20.235
Don't worry about him. 

595
01:02:22.612 --> 01:02:24.364
Little guy's gonna be okay. 

596
01:02:26.533 --> 01:02:28.535
Sorry. I found these 
in your kitchen. 

597
01:02:32.372 --> 01:02:34.165
I was alone 
when I was his age. 

598
01:02:35.041 --> 01:02:36.584
I had to fend for myself. 

599
01:02:41.965 --> 01:02:43.216
He's lucky he has you. 

600
01:02:44.092 --> 01:02:46.970
Well. you didn't 
turn out half bad. 

601
01:02:48.388 --> 01:02:52.017
Mmm. Life's messy. 
but we do the best we can. 

602
01:02:53.601 --> 01:02:55.270
Listen. I called a gunrunner 

603
01:02:55.353 --> 01:02:57.105
who agreed to take you 
out of the system. 

604
01:02:57.158 --> 01:02:59.035
We both know the Twins 
will be looking for you. 

605
01:02:59.119 --> 01:03:00.495
so you best keep moving. 

606
01:03:25.729 --> 01:03:27.105
Thank you. Mando. 

607
01:03:27.188 --> 01:03:28.648
It was a fair trade. 

608
01:03:28.732 --> 01:03:30.650
Make sure you lay low. 

609
01:03:30.734 --> 01:03:33.069
I don't wanna see your name 
on my list again. 

610
01:03:33.153 --> 01:03:34.362
You have my word. 

611
01:03:35.488 --> 01:03:37.741
All right. you take care 
of yourself. little guy. 

612
01:03:39.284 --> 01:03:42.203
And keep an eye on 
your old man. too. all right? 

613
01:03:43.204 --> 01:03:44.581
Here you go. 

614
01:03:44.664 --> 01:03:46.374
Hang on to these for me. 

615
01:04:27.552 --> 01:04:29.888
Let's save the rest of these 
for after dinner. 

616
01:05:47.686 --> 01:05:49.562
Wake up. 

617
01:05:49.646 --> 01:05:50.647
Oh. What? Uh. 

618
01:05:50.730 --> 01:05:52.065
~Wake up. 
-What's going on? 

619
01:05:52.148 --> 01:05:53.400
There's someone out there. 

620
01:05:53.483 --> 01:05:54.943
I'll be awake in the morning. 

621
01:05:55.026 --> 01:05:56.861
Quiet. Get under the floor. 

622
01:06:08.760 --> 01:06:12.055
Wait here. 
If I signal. get out. 

623
01:06:32.867 --> 01:06:35.245
Shh. Shh. Shh. 

624
01:07:23.346 --> 01:07:26.433
Help! It got me! It got me! 

625
01:07:26.516 --> 01:07:28.727
Keibu. 

626
01:08:21.666 --> 01:08:23.835
Did you get the Mandalorian? 

627
01:08:25.086 --> 01:08:28.882
Very good. Bring him to Nal Hutta. 

628
01:08:36.973 --> 01:08:38.517
Help me! Help! 

629
01:09:38.922 --> 01:09:41.133
Ow. 

630
01:09:42.676 --> 01:09:44.928
Ow. ow. ow. 

631
01:09:46.805 --> 01:09:48.056
Let him go. 

632
01:09:54.938 --> 01:09:56.690
Hey. you hungry? 

633
01:10:00.914 --> 01:10:02.415
You want a treat? 

634
01:10:04.251 --> 01:10:05.669
Here you go. 

635
01:10:05.752 --> 01:10:07.546
Good girl. 

636
01:10:08.839 --> 01:10:09.840
Come on. Come on! 

637
01:10:09.923 --> 01:10:11.967
Uh-oh. 

638
01:10:12.050 --> 01:10:13.385
Oh. 

639
01:10:33.113 --> 01:10:34.781
Uh-oh. 

640
01:10:39.828 --> 01:10:41.455
Who hired you? 

641
01:10:42.205 --> 01:10:43.665
Was it the Hutts? 

642
01:10:45.208 --> 01:10:46.793
Well. if it was the Hutts. 

643
01:10:46.877 --> 01:10:48.962
I'd make sure they're 
paying you what you're worth. 

644
01:10:49.045 --> 01:10:50.714
But I'm guessing a Kyuzo 
is smart enough 

645
01:10:50.797 --> 01:10:51.798
to get their money up-front-- 

646
01:12:48.855 --> 01:12:50.857
Nal Hutta. 

647
01:12:50.941 --> 01:12:54.152
The Hutts are there. 
I don't like it. 

648
01:13:13.975 --> 01:13:15.769
Oh! Wow! Oh. I'm coming. 

649
01:13:23.694 --> 01:13:24.903
Kid. don't be scared. 

650
01:13:24.986 --> 01:13:26.738
Don't be scared. 
It's okay. yeah. 

651
01:13:26.822 --> 01:13:27.906
Come on. let's go. 

652
01:13:27.989 --> 01:13:29.700
Oh... 

653
01:13:40.127 --> 01:13:43.213
Oh! Hello! 
It's me. it's me! You're here. 

654
01:13:43.296 --> 01:13:46.008
You came for me! You found me! 

655
01:13:47.342 --> 01:13:49.052
Oh. we thought you were dead. 

656
01:13:50.012 --> 01:13:51.596
Mandalorian. he saved me. 

657
01:13:51.680 --> 01:13:53.724
Big guy. He's inside there. 

658
01:13:53.807 --> 01:13:55.684
Yeah. we got to go 
and find him 

659
01:13:55.737 --> 01:13:57.531
and bring him home 
for the baby. 

660
01:13:59.408 --> 01:14:02.369
The big thing. The big dog. 
The big dog. The big... 

661
01:14:02.452 --> 01:14:04.454
Oh. oh. It picked me up... 

662
01:14:15.590 --> 01:14:18.135
Mando is in there. 
In the palace. 

663
01:14:30.897 --> 01:14:32.566
Come on. Up. up. up. up. 

664
01:14:32.649 --> 01:14:34.484
Come on. baby. You can do it. 

665
01:14:42.784 --> 01:14:44.536
Big pipe. huh? 

666
01:15:12.909 --> 01:15:14.411
Good shot. baby. 

667
01:15:36.683 --> 01:15:39.102
Pay the hunter. 

668
01:15:54.701 --> 01:15:57.871
You broke our agreement. 

669
01:15:57.925 --> 01:16:00.093
Now you must pay. 

670
01:16:00.886 --> 01:16:02.554
Bring me his helmet. 

671
01:16:12.648 --> 01:16:15.525
Mandalorian steel. 

672
01:16:15.609 --> 01:16:19.321
Priceless on the black market. 

673
01:16:20.697 --> 01:16:24.117
But worth even more is knowing 

674
01:16:24.201 --> 01:16:27.913
we have shamed you forever. 

675
01:16:28.538 --> 01:16:31.291
We know the Mandalorian Creed. 

676
01:16:31.833 --> 01:16:33.585
You will be outcast 

677
01:16:33.669 --> 01:16:37.089
for letting an enemy see 
your face. 

678
01:16:37.756 --> 01:16:39.383
Not if you all die. 

679
01:16:43.095 --> 01:16:46.473
It will bring us ecstasy 

680
01:16:46.556 --> 01:16:51.395
to watch 
your strong spirit break. 

681
01:17:00.457 --> 01:17:01.458
Monsters. 

682
01:17:02.167 --> 01:17:03.877
You did this to him. 

683
01:17:03.961 --> 01:17:07.256
Rotta would have 
died painlessly. 

684
01:17:07.339 --> 01:17:08.757
but you betrayed us. 

685
01:17:09.258 --> 01:17:12.761
Now he will suffer 
for centuries. 

686
01:17:13.303 --> 01:17:18.350
You see. Hutts live for 
hundreds of years. 

687
01:17:19.142 --> 01:17:23.689
Just like 
your small. green child. 

688
01:17:24.189 --> 01:17:26.275
One day you will die. 

689
01:17:26.358 --> 01:17:30.237
and Grogu will be without you 
to protect him. 

690
01:17:30.320 --> 01:17:34.199
And then. 
it will be his turn to suffer. 

691
01:20:27.074 --> 01:20:29.660
You have entertained us. 

692
01:20:30.452 --> 01:20:32.704
Here is your reward. 

693
01:22:31.764 --> 01:22:33.766
Uh-oh. Which way? 

694
01:23:38.342 --> 01:23:42.054
Even if 
you win. you will die from the poison. 

695
01:24:08.175 --> 01:24:09.301
Dank farrik. 

696
01:24:12.638 --> 01:24:13.889
Get out! Go! 

697
01:24:16.016 --> 01:24:18.018
Come on. go! Go. go! 

698
01:24:32.574 --> 01:24:35.411
-Oh. yeah! 
-Wow! 

699
01:24:35.494 --> 01:24:36.870
Wait. Wait. 

700
01:25:05.285 --> 01:25:06.954
You okay? 

701
01:25:12.918 --> 01:25:15.337
~How did you get here? 
~We Got a ship. 

702
01:25:15.421 --> 01:25:16.880
That way. Let's go! 

703
01:25:23.512 --> 01:25:27.266
Send the droids! 
Release the Amani! Don't let him escape! 

704
01:25:52.958 --> 01:25:54.752
This way. This way. yeah. 

705
01:26:06.817 --> 01:26:08.611
This way! 

706
01:26:15.034 --> 01:26:16.785
Up. up. up. up. going up! 

707
01:26:16.869 --> 01:26:18.787
I don't want to fall. 
I don't want to. 

708
01:26:19.496 --> 01:26:20.497
Go! 

709
01:26:20.581 --> 01:26:22.708
Yeah. Okay. okay. Yeah. 
Let's go. 

710
01:26:35.554 --> 01:26:37.931
Go. kid. 
I can't fit in that thing. 

711
01:26:39.224 --> 01:26:40.976
but you have to leave. 

712
01:26:43.520 --> 01:26:44.730
Don't worry. 

713
01:26:45.356 --> 01:26:47.066
I'll be right behind you. 

714
01:26:51.236 --> 01:26:53.656
Go now. I'll hold them off. 

715
01:26:54.198 --> 01:26:56.116
We'll come back 
for you. Mando. 

716
01:26:59.924 --> 01:27:01.175
Come on. baby. 

717
01:27:01.258 --> 01:27:03.135
Don't worry. We'll be back. 

718
01:27:03.218 --> 01:27:05.471
Yeah. let's go. Let's go. 

719
01:27:05.554 --> 01:27:06.722
Come on. baby. 

720
01:28:37.700 --> 01:28:39.076
Goodbye. kid. 

721
01:31:33.160 --> 01:31:34.954
No life force detected. 

722
01:37:32.715 --> 01:37:35.426
Methinks you are 
the one who stole my fish. 

723
01:37:49.523 --> 01:37:52.193
I'm guessing 
you're not from around here. 

724
01:37:56.125 --> 01:37:59.128
A morsel like you 
should be more careful. 

725
01:37:59.211 --> 01:38:02.715
You look to be the bottom 
of the Nal Hutta food chain. 

726
01:38:04.216 --> 01:38:06.260
I'm surprised 
you haven't found your way 

727
01:38:06.344 --> 01:38:08.095
to the Hutts' supper table. 

728
01:38:10.681 --> 01:38:12.516
You've heard of the Hutts. 
have you? 

729
01:38:13.726 --> 01:38:14.977
Are you scared? 

730
01:38:16.771 --> 01:38:17.897
You should be. 

731
01:38:18.397 --> 01:38:21.359
They would swallow you whole 
given half a chance. 

732
01:38:25.863 --> 01:38:27.657
Make yourself scarce. 

733
01:38:50.513 --> 01:38:51.472
Uh-huh. 

734
01:39:26.477 --> 01:39:27.645
Hey. 

735
01:39:29.522 --> 01:39:30.940
Get away from my fish. 

736
01:39:36.153 --> 01:39:37.780
Keibu. 

737
01:39:58.354 --> 01:40:00.356
The hunter says 
you have a partner. 

738
01:40:01.983 --> 01:40:04.902
Says you two 
escaped the Twins. 

739
01:40:04.986 --> 01:40:06.863
Well. that's impressive. 

740
01:40:12.535 --> 01:40:15.246
Says your partner's 
hurt real bad. 

741
01:40:15.329 --> 01:40:18.583
Bit by a dragonsnake. 
Poisoned. 

742
01:40:22.753 --> 01:40:25.047
I want you 
to feed this to him. 

743
01:40:27.341 --> 01:40:28.342
Now. you should know. 

744
01:40:28.426 --> 01:40:30.511
this might be too little. 
too late. 

745
01:40:31.012 --> 01:40:33.764
and there's a good chance 
he doesn't wake up. 

746
01:40:38.186 --> 01:40:40.188
Either way. 
best thing you can do 

747
01:40:40.271 --> 01:40:41.856
right now 
is make him comfortable. 

748
01:40:42.815 --> 01:40:45.985
There comes a time where 
we all have to say goodbye. 

749
01:40:53.242 --> 01:40:55.661
I wish you luck. 
small traveler. 

750
01:43:43.489 --> 01:43:44.532
Hey. kiddo. 

751
01:43:50.329 --> 01:43:51.664
The old protect the young. 

752
01:43:51.747 --> 01:43:53.541
and then the young 
protect the old. 

753
01:43:54.637 --> 01:43:55.972
This is the Way. 

754
01:43:59.142 --> 01:44:00.810
Now how do we 
get off this planet? 

755
01:44:07.984 --> 01:44:10.528
That's the gunrunner 
that was carrying Rotta. 

756
01:46:23.599 --> 01:46:27.311
Well. kid. the way I see it 
we got two choices. 

757
01:46:28.021 --> 01:46:30.481
We can use this ship. 
Get off world. 

758
01:46:31.149 --> 01:46:33.651
That might buy us some time. 
A little bit of peace. 

759
01:46:34.152 --> 01:46:36.362
But the Hutts 
will keep coming for us. 

760
01:46:37.447 --> 01:46:39.198
Just like they came for Rotta. 

761
01:46:42.326 --> 01:46:43.411
So. do we run? 

762
01:46:47.707 --> 01:46:48.791
Or do we fight? 

763
01:47:32.805 --> 01:47:34.599
Huh? 

764
01:47:50.531 --> 01:47:52.325
Repel the intruders! 

765
01:47:52.408 --> 01:47:53.910
Roger. roger! 

766
01:47:54.547 --> 01:47:55.965
Protect the palace! 

767
01:47:56.049 --> 01:47:56.966
Affirmative. 

768
01:48:06.517 --> 01:48:07.644
Follow my lead. 

769
01:48:12.065 --> 01:48:13.149
Fire! 

770
01:48:24.118 --> 01:48:25.703
Come on. Come on. 

771
01:49:04.462 --> 01:49:06.005
On me. 

772
01:49:49.716 --> 01:49:50.717
Fall back! 

773
01:52:27.325 --> 01:52:29.410
Wait! We know much. 

774
01:52:29.494 --> 01:52:30.995
Go help Rotta. 

775
01:52:39.212 --> 01:52:40.755
You saw my face. 

776
01:52:41.673 --> 01:52:42.423
Stop! 

777
01:52:43.424 --> 01:52:44.926
Now it's time to die. 

778
01:53:53.977 --> 01:53:55.061
Leave him alone! 

779
01:54:17.250 --> 01:54:20.044
You don't have Jabba to protect you. 

780
01:54:20.628 --> 01:54:22.088
I'm not little anymore! 

781
01:55:53.370 --> 01:55:56.623
Stop! You'll kill us all! 

782
01:56:41.209 --> 01:56:42.752
Save us. bounty hunter! 

783
01:56:44.129 --> 01:56:45.130
Keibu. 

784
01:56:45.213 --> 01:56:46.881
Save us! 

785
01:57:21.219 --> 01:57:23.888
We don't have much time. 
We have to get out of here. 

786
01:57:24.848 --> 01:57:26.057
Is there another way out? 

787
01:57:26.141 --> 01:57:28.810
-I think it's that way. 
-Go. Go! 

788
01:57:45.326 --> 01:57:46.244
Target sighted. 

789
01:58:12.240 --> 01:58:13.158
Hello? 

790
01:58:13.241 --> 01:58:15.118
Mando! We came back. 

791
01:58:15.201 --> 01:58:16.453
~what? 
~We came back. 

792
01:58:16.536 --> 01:58:18.246
We told you we would. 

793
01:58:25.295 --> 01:58:28.256
Adelphi Squadron. 
entering atmosphere. 

794
01:58:29.215 --> 01:58:31.926
-What's your status. Mando? 
-We're under attack. 

795
01:58:32.927 --> 01:58:34.262
There are too many. 

796
01:58:34.346 --> 01:58:36.348
Fire everything you have 
at my location. 

797
01:58:37.891 --> 01:58:41.102
~Your location? 
~Yes. my location. 

798
01:58:41.186 --> 01:58:42.687
I can't give that order. 

799
01:58:42.771 --> 01:58:44.189
Don't worry... 

800
01:58:46.191 --> 01:58:48.401
we'll be out of here 
by the time you do. 

801
01:58:50.028 --> 01:58:51.071
Good luck. 

802
01:58:54.628 --> 01:58:55.920
Blue Leader to squadron. 

803
01:58:56.504 --> 01:58:59.549
assume defensive formation. 
prepare to engage. 

804
01:58:59.633 --> 01:59:00.800
All weapons hot. 

805
01:59:00.884 --> 01:59:01.718
Copy that. 

806
01:59:19.361 --> 01:59:21.112
Enemy fighters approaching. 

807
01:59:23.281 --> 01:59:24.157
Here they come. 

808
01:59:51.476 --> 01:59:52.811
Turbolasers. up ahead. 

809
01:59:52.894 --> 01:59:54.062
Got it. 

810
02:00:14.958 --> 02:00:16.376
I've got one on my tail. 

811
02:00:19.087 --> 02:00:20.588
I got you. 

812
02:00:30.765 --> 02:00:32.392
Yippee! Yay! 

813
02:00:32.475 --> 02:00:34.060
Taking out the launch tubes. 

814
02:00:41.818 --> 02:00:44.696
Blue Leader to Red Jammer. 
mark it and lock it in. 

815
02:00:47.198 --> 02:00:48.325
Locking in target. 

816
02:00:52.037 --> 02:00:53.079
It's a dead end. 

817
02:00:54.342 --> 02:00:55.760
We're trapped. 

818
02:00:56.469 --> 02:00:57.679
Stand back. 

819
02:01:04.060 --> 02:01:05.395
We're closing fast. 

820
02:01:05.478 --> 02:01:06.896
Repeat. we're closing fast. 

821
02:01:06.980 --> 02:01:08.565
You better be 
out of there. Mando. 

822
02:01:08.648 --> 02:01:10.066
Jump. 

823
02:01:10.150 --> 02:01:12.235
That's a long way down. 

824
02:01:12.319 --> 02:01:13.528
Closing on target. 

825
02:01:15.071 --> 02:01:17.365
~Gotta jump. 
-Moat's not that deep. 

826
02:01:17.449 --> 02:01:19.492
It's a bomber. Jump. 

827
02:01:19.576 --> 02:01:21.369
Let's light up this swamp. 

828
02:01:56.166 --> 02:01:57.792
Anybody got eyes on Mando? 

829
02:01:58.460 --> 02:01:59.461
There they are. 

830
02:02:03.882 --> 02:02:07.636
Zeb. go collect the trash. 

831
02:02:15.769 --> 02:02:18.563
I'm getting a little tired 
of these hot extractions. 

832
02:02:19.481 --> 02:02:21.441
What took you so long? 

833
02:02:22.776 --> 02:02:23.902
Hop in. 

834
02:02:23.985 --> 02:02:25.820
Let's head home. 

835
02:02:48.760 --> 02:02:50.136
Colonel. 

836
02:02:52.442 --> 02:02:53.818
Messy. 

837
02:02:54.402 --> 02:02:55.654
Very messy. 

838
02:02:56.863 --> 02:02:58.490
Why'd you come for me? 

839
02:02:58.573 --> 02:03:00.075
That wasn't part 
of the mission. 

840
02:03:00.825 --> 02:03:03.954
You were right. 
Coin told us everything. 

841
02:03:04.454 --> 02:03:06.081
The Twins were playing us. 

842
02:03:06.164 --> 02:03:08.708
Feeding information 
to the Empire all along. 

843
02:03:10.043 --> 02:03:12.712
They picked a side. 
It wasn't ours. 

844
02:03:13.338 --> 02:03:16.967
Besides. 
we don't leave our own behind. 

845
02:03:17.509 --> 02:03:19.302
I'm an independent contractor. 

846
02:03:19.386 --> 02:03:22.347
Sure. Mando. Sure you are. 

847
02:03:33.024 --> 02:03:34.943
Can I give you a ride 
somewhere? 

848
02:03:35.026 --> 02:03:37.237
Actually. I was thinking 
I could stay here. 

849
02:03:38.029 --> 02:03:39.823
Maybe work 
for the New Republic. 

850
02:03:40.407 --> 02:03:42.826
Don't take this 
the wrong way. but... 

851
02:03:42.909 --> 02:03:44.995
I'm not sure you would fit in. 

852
02:03:45.078 --> 02:03:46.913
You know... 

853
02:03:46.997 --> 02:03:49.249
...I might have 
a uniform that would fit him. 

854
02:03:50.292 --> 02:03:53.169
Come on. 
let me buy you a drink. 

855
02:03:54.933 --> 02:03:57.477
Thank you. Mando. 
I owe you big time. 

856
02:03:57.561 --> 02:03:58.895
Just doing my job. 

857
02:03:59.521 --> 02:04:00.522
And keep an eye on him. 

858
02:04:01.648 --> 02:04:03.275
Your dad's 
one of the good ones. 

859
02:04:17.747 --> 02:04:19.040
Come on. big guy. 

860
02:04:20.208 --> 02:04:22.586
Watch your step. 
First round's on me. 

861
02:04:31.761 --> 02:04:33.889
Hey. kid. Come up here. 

862
02:04:53.545 --> 02:04:54.754
Your turn. 

863
02:04:57.674 --> 02:04:58.675
Go ahead.
